From a writing standpoint, I can't say it adds anything, and I get the issue with interdependence, but it still irks me that there seems to be a relatively easy fix to an issue and no one's even considered it. If you can reasonably negate the premise, why shouldn't you?

As it stands, the SCP has a sibling in SCP-910 as an unsettling idea, it falls short of being engaging; as it is now it looks like the Foundation tried to research the issue, lost interest, and just put him in a coma to keep him out of his misery. That's not frightening, that's FEMA.

tl;dr I know it's against protocol, but in the larger scope, half of the article would quickly become moot.







