23 Aug 2011 02:35






Well, the thing is:

A) in-universe cross-testing SCPs can have highly unexpected negative effects, especially when we just don't know how the SCPs work (which is most of them, including 138 and 427).

B) since there is no canon, we can freely assume that 138 and 427 do not exist in the same universes. Or, alternatively, that there's some Big Reason that 138 and 427 can't be cross-tested, but it's just not stated in the article because your clearance isn't high enough to see those articles.

C) There are other in-universe reasons for not trying to de-SCP-ify SCPs. Studying them, for one.

Any of those things can be handwaved into irrelevance with ease, of course, but when the proposal adds nothing from a writing standpoint whatsoever why, exactly, should they be handwaved?







