If there's a reason, then let a response from O5 or something shoot the proposal down; it implies some greater mystery as to why official orders are preventing this. Furthermore, there doesn't seem to be any research being done, medical or otherwise. Testing X with Y and getting Rape is one of the few things that would make things like that worth it. Say they do approve it, but something blows up in our faces and now he's part fleshbeast and immortal. That quickly becomes something not only believable in terms of research mishaps, but activates (if faintly) my  sense.

I guess what I'm saying is, it doesn't add anything to the article but rather subtracts any holes someone would care to poke in it.







